commit.message: Make markdownlint happy with CHANGELOG
Update changelog

Added the cupcake file

Added the cupcake a new cow to the existing list of cows :)
Add alpaca.cow

Revert cowthink.1 to point to cowsay.1 in the same dir

For a source tree from git or tarball, if the cowthink.1
file in the source tree is `.so cowsay.1`, running
`man ./cowthink.1` will open the `cowsay.1` file from the
source tree, which is OK.

HOWEVER, if the `cowthink.1` file in the source tree is
`.so man1/cowsay.1`, running `man ./cowthink.1` will either
show the **wrong** man page from `/usr/share/man/man1/cowsay.1`
(or elsewhere in MANPATH, I presume), or if no `cowsay.1` file
is found in MANPATH, will show an **empty** page.

That is clearly wrong, so reverting to the old `cowthink.1`
file which points `man` to the `cowsay.1` file in the same
directory is clearly better.

Split man page options list into sections

The OPTIONS list in the man page is very long. Separating it
into subsections helps read the long list.

The fact that the options have already been ordered in a way
which already groups them into those sections indicates that
these sections make sense.

I have no idea why the cowthink.1 file changes on `make man`,
but I accept that `make man` knows what it is doing.

commit.message:
convert non-extension mech-and-cow to *.cow format

Convert the non-extension mech-and-cow file to the *.cow
format, taking some hints from the MechAndCow.pm source
for the location of the $thoughts line, and from the
default.cow file for the $eyes and $tongue.

The mech-and-cow.cow file can probably be removed in the
future once the *.pm format has been implemented.

The $thoughts line to the bubble ends quite far away from
the left edge of the screen (column 18) which looks weird
for narrow messages, but other cows end even further to
the right (e.g dragon-and-cow.cow in column 23), so this
should be ok.

commit.message:
Remove trailing spaces

When generating the balloon, don't add any trailing spaces.

Trailing spaces may break formatting of cowsay-based e-mail signature:
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=276144

This patch is shipped in Debian/Ubuntu:
https://salsa.debian.org/debian/cowsay/-/blob/master/debian/patches/02-remove_trailing_spaces

Also in Fedora/EPEL:
https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/cowsay/blob/master/f/cowsay-3.03-debian-02-remove_trailing_spaces.patch

Tested:
```
$ ./cowsay 'No trailing spaces' | cat -A
 ____________________$
< No trailing spaces >$
 --------------------$
        \   ^__^$
         \  (oo)\_______$
            (__)\       )\/\$
                ||----w |$
                ||     ||$
```

Before this commit:
```
$ ./cowsay 'Trailing spaces :-(' | cat -A
 _____________________ $
< Trailing spaces :-( >$
 --------------------- $
        \   ^__^$
         \  (oo)\_______$
            (__)\       )\/\$
                ||----w |$
                ||     ||$
```

Empty message results in broken baloon

Debian bug entry for this issue:
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=165218

A patch for this issue is shipped in Debian/Ubuntu:
https://salsa.debian.org/debian/cowsay/-/blob/master/debian/patches/01-empty_messages_fix

Also same patch in Fedora/EPEL:
https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/cowsay/blob/master/f/cowsay-3.03-debian-01-empty_messages_fix.patch

This is a different fix, but it essentially does the same.

Tested:

```
$ echo -n '' | ./cowsay
 __
<  >
 --
        \   ^__^
         \  (oo)\_______
            (__)\       )\/\
                ||----w |
                ||     ||
```

Before this commit:

```
$ echo -n '' | ./cowsay
 _
<   >
 -
        \   ^__^
         \  (oo)\_______
            (__)\       )\/\
                ||----w |
                ||     ||
```

Add a fox to cowsay

Original author Hansen Wu has released it under the same license
terms as cowsay:
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=888229

`fox.cow` is already shipped with the Debian/Ubuntu package for cowsay.

Removed trailing whitespace from `fox.cow` (matches the one in the
Debian package.)

Tested:

```
$ ./cowsay -f ./share/cows/fox.cow 'Crazy like a fox!'
 ___________________
< Crazy like a fox! >
 -------------------
         \     ,-.      .-,
          \    |-.\ __ /.-|
           \   \  `    `  /
                /_     _ \
              <  _`q  p _  >
              <.._=/  \=_. >
                 {`\()/`}`\
                 {      }  \
                 |{    }    \
                 \ '--'   .- \
                 |-      /    \
                 | | | | |     ;
                 | | |.;.,..__ |
               .-"";`         `|
              /    |           /
              `-../____,..---'`
```
